txt.en: 'Few joys in this world are as pure as sitting on a dock and casting a line into the waves.'
'If you travel north to Duillond, give my regards to Master Dorongúr.'
'The dwarf-port to the north, called by them Kheledûl, could not be more different than this, my Celondim.'
'The Sea gives only what bounty it chooses to.'
'I certainly did! The sea was generous today.'
